Usage:
	Just add this script to the source dir of your cmake-project.
	Now you can build and install your project similar to an
	autotools-project with the following commands:

	./configure
	make
	make install

	As of now the configure script only supports the following options:
	CC
	CXX
	--prefix
	--srcdir
	--enable-debug
	--enable-*

	--enable-foo-bar for example adds -DFOO_BAR=ON to the cmake-call
	--enable-foo-bar=off add -DFOO_BAR=off to the cmake-call

	Example: 
	./configure CC=/usr/bin/gcc CXX=/usr/bin/g++ --prefix=/usr --enable-debug
